        Fix failing instanceof when reading context
    </title>
    <updated>2017-04-22T17:14:16Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Fix failing instanceof when reading context

`instanceof HTMLCanvasElement/CanvasRenderingContext2D` fails when the item is inside an iframe or when running in a protected environment. We could guess the types from their toString() value but let&amp;#39;s keep things flexible and assume it&amp;#39;s a sufficient condition if the item has a context2D which has item as `canvas`.&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
